Cell["\<\
The quantum Schur transform is a unitary change of basis from the \
computational product basis to the Schur basis, a basis designated by the \
irreducible representations of the symmetric and unitary groups. More \
specifically, it implements the Schur-Weyl duality and decomposes the total \
Hilbert space for a collection of many multi-level quantum systems into \
irreducible orthogonal subspaces that are invariant under the symmetric and \
unitary groups. Given the abundance of such collections in physics, the \
quantum Schur transform finds a wide range of applications. Notably, it is \
utilized in numerous quantum information protocols for optimal purification \
and spectrum estimation, universal entanglement concentration and source \
coding, decoherence-free subspaces and subsystems, sample-efficient state \
tomography, and quantum communications without a shared reference frame.\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1970639134,ExpressionUUID->"f32439f7-7310-4a71-891f-81685f6881c4"],

Cell[TextData[{
 "Q3 provides two implementations of the quantum Schur transform, ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData["SchurBasis"]], "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/SchurBasis", 
    "QuantumMob Package Symbol"},
   "PackageLink",
   BaseStyle->"InlineFormula"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "101c6ec3-ece1-4db4-8a6e-6f38501104a6"],
 " and ",
 Cell[BoxData[
  TemplateBox[{
    Cell[
     TextData["DualSchurBasis"]], "paclet:QuantumMob/Q3/ref/DualSchurBasis", 
    "QuantumMob Package Symbol"},
   "PackageLink",
   BaseStyle->"InlineFormula"]], "InlineFormula",
  FontFamily->"Source Sans Pro",ExpressionUUID->
  "046f2db5-11fd-4bcf-8d97-6513659e19b7"],
 ", following the ",
 StyleBox["Bacon-Chuang-Harrow ",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 "and ",
 StyleBox["Korvi algorithms",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", respectively. Both are known to exhibit exponential speedup over \
classical algorithms."
}], "TechNoteText",
 CellID->1121935350,ExpressionUUID->"89130137-0913-469f-81c7-b25f99703faa"],

Cell["\<\
This tutorial explains and illustrates the principle behind the \
Bacon-Chuang-Harrow algorithm.\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->14776229,ExpressionUUID->"50d9d3a2-fe3a-4607-b89c-2654ab323081"],

