Cell["\<\
\tOf course, standard Young tableaux are a special case of Weyl tableaux, \
where the dimension and the degree are identical. They can be converted to \
Gelfand patterns, and vice versa. Again with the example discussed above, we \
have\
\>", "TechNoteText",
 CellID->2015257401,ExpressionUUID->"c556af5e-8d46-4c51-b6ee-b53fcd82232b"],

