TaggingRules->{
 "ModificationHighlight" -> False, "ColorType" -> "", "LinkTrails" -> "", 
  "ExampleCounter" -> 1, 
  "Openers" -> {
   "PrimaryExamplesSection" -> Open, "ExampleSection" -> {"0" -> Open}}, 
  "NewStyles" -> True, "CitationPopupData" -> {"2021", ""}, "ShowCitation" -> 
  False, "RootCaptions" -> "", "HeaderCoreAreaLink" -> {}, 
  "Metadata" -> {
   "built" -> "{2026, 4, 12, 18, 0, 13.588055}", 
    "history" -> {"13", "", "", ""}, "context" -> "QuantumMob`Q3`", 
    "keywords" -> {
     "Schur-Weyl duality", "Schur basis", "quantum Schur transform"}, 
    "specialkeywords" -> {}, "tutorialcollectionlinks" -> {}, "index" -> True,
     "label" -> "Quantum Mob/ Q3 Tech Note", "language" -> "en", "paclet" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3", "status" -> "None", "summary" -> 
    "The quantum Schur transform is a unitary change of basis from the \
computational product basis to the Schur basis, a basis designated by the \
irreducible representations of the symmetric and unitary groups. More \
specifically, it implements the Schur-Weyl duality and decomposes the total \
Hilbert space for a collection of many multi-level quantum systems into \
irreducible orthogonal subspaces that are invariant under the symmetric and \
unitary groups. Given the abundance of such collections in physics, the \
quantum Schur transform finds a wide range of applications. Notably, it is \
utilized in numerous quantum information protocols for optimal purification \
and spectrum estimation, universal entanglement concentration and source \
coding, decoherence-free subspaces and subsystems, sample-efficient state \
tomography, and quantum communications without a shared reference frame. Q3 \
provides two implementations of the quantum Schur transform, SchurBasis and \
DualSchurBasis, following the Bacon-Chuang-Harrow and Korvi algorithms, \
respectively. Both are known to exhibit exponential speedup over classical \
algorithms. This tutorial explains and illustrates the principle behind the \
Bacon-Chuang-Harrow algorithm.", "synonyms" -> {}, "tabletags" -> {}, "title" -> 
    "Quantum Schur Transform", "titlemodifier" -> "", "metadescription" -> "",
     "windowtitle" -> "Quantum Schur Transform", "type" -> "Tech Note", "uri" -> 
    "QuantumMob/Q3/tutorial/QuantumSchurTransform"}},
